five or 10 minutes a day.

00:02:18.990 --> 00:02:20.910 align:middle line:84%
And it really is--
immediate results

00:02:20.910 --> 00:02:22.910 align:middle line:84%
happen when you start
plugging into this energy.

00:02:22.910 --> 00:02:24.200 align:middle line:90%
>> You're so right.

00:02:24.200 --> 00:02:26.700 align:middle line:84%
You know, until you said
that, I didn't realize it.

00:02:26.700 --> 00:02:27.500 align:middle line:90%
But you're right.

00:02:27.500 --> 00:02:31.730 align:middle line:84%
We're taught-- we're taught
that we don't have it.

00:02:31.730 --> 00:02:32.660 align:middle line:90%
Why is that?

00:02:32.660 --> 00:02:33.710 align:middle line:90%
Are people afraid of it?

00:02:33.710 --> 00:02:35.600 align:middle line:90%
Were our parents afraid of it?

00:02:35.600 --> 00:02:37.110 align:middle line:90%
Were their parents afraid of it?

00:02:37.110 --> 00:02:37.850 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah, you know what?

00:02:37.850 --> 00:02:38.660 align:middle line:90%
I guess so.

00:02:38.660 --> 00:02:41.730 align:middle line:84%
I don't-- I always rejected
what I was always--

00:02:41.730 --> 00:02:44.573 align:middle line:84%
even when I was in high
school and I became interested

00:02:44.573 --> 00:02:46.490 align:middle line:84%
in this, I would go to
the library and look up

00:02:46.490 --> 00:02:47.550 align:middle line:90%
in the esoteric section.

00:02:47.550 --> 00:02:48.650 align:middle line:84%
And I would get all
these books out.

00:02:48.650 --> 00:02:51.150 align:middle line:84%
And they all said, oh, well,
you have to stand on your head,

00:02:51.150 --> 00:02:53.660 align:middle line:84%
and meditate for 20 hours,
and give up all your worldly

00:02:53.660 --> 00:02:54.500 align:middle line:90%
possessions.

00:02:54.500 --> 00:02:55.830 align:middle line:90%
And it's not true.

00:02:55.830 --> 00:02:58.430 align:middle line:84%
You can have great
things and have

00:02:58.430 --> 00:03:02.080 align:middle line:84%
a great sense of inner
power at the same time.

00:03:02.080 --> 00:03:03.200 align:middle line:10%
And you don't have to--

00:03:03.200 --> 00:03:06.140 align:middle line:10%
I think way back when,
someone shysted us and said

00:03:06.140 --> 00:03:08.360 align:middle line:10%
that we had to give up all
our worldly possessions

00:03:08.360 --> 00:03:14.000 align:middle line:10%
and all our desires in order
to be spiritual in this sense.

00:03:14.000 --> 00:03:16.770 align:middle line:10%
And it's just not true.

00:03:16.770 --> 00:03:19.460 align:middle line:10%
I just-- I also think there
wasn't a need to connect

00:03:19.460 --> 00:03:20.750 align:middle line:10%
with it as there is today.

00:03:20.750 --> 00:03:23.250 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes, very important point.

00:03:23.250 --> 00:03:27.770 align:middle line:84%
>> I think that way back when
my parents were growing up,

00:03:27.770 --> 00:03:29.570 align:middle line:84%
they had an ideal
for themselves,

00:03:29.570 --> 00:03:32.010 align:middle line:84%
and it didn't include
this sixth sense.

00:03:32.010 --> 00:03:35.120 align:middle line:84%
And there was rules
that were just--

00:03:35.120 --> 00:03:36.500 align:middle line:90%
society lived by certain rules.

00:03:36.500 --> 00:03:38.540 align:middle line:90%
And there are no rules today.

00:03:38.540 --> 00:03:40.340 align:middle line:84%
And you can even look
at the stock market

00:03:40.340 --> 00:03:44.130 align:middle line:84%
and look at the way we live our
lives, and there are no rules.

00:03:44.130 --> 00:03:48.320 align:middle line:84%
And I think that we need--
that sixth sense is the rule,

00:03:48.320 --> 00:03:52.880 align:middle line:90%
is the way to get--

00:03:52.880 --> 00:03:56.660 align:middle line:84%
to be safe, and to prosper,
and to enhance your life

00:03:56.660 --> 00:03:58.920 align:middle line:84%
in such a way that you can
have everything you want.

00:03:58.920 --> 00:04:00.295 align:middle line:84%
>> And here's
what's interesting.

00:04:00.295 --> 00:04:03.470 align:middle line:84%
Your generation-- what
are you, Generation Xers?

00:04:03.470 --> 00:04:05.010 align:middle line:90%
Is that--

00:04:05.010 --> 00:04:05.960 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:04:05.960 --> 00:04:07.550 align:middle line:84%
Yeah, one of the older
versions of the Gen Xers, yes.

00:04:07.550 --> 00:04:10.070 align:middle line:84%
>> You're one of the older
versions out of the Generation

00:04:10.070 --> 00:04:12.050 align:middle line:90%
Xers.

00:04:12.050 --> 00:04:18.940 align:middle line:84%
Have the Gen Xers become, in a
sense, the teachers of today?

00:04:18.940 --> 00:04:20.690 align:middle line:84%
>> I think-- this is
the thing with Gen X.

00:04:20.690 --> 00:04:23.270 align:middle line:84%
When we were first
graduating from college,

00:04:23.270 --> 00:04:25.730 align:middle line:84%
people used to say, oh,
we're such slackers,

00:04:25.730 --> 00:04:31.700 align:middle line:84%
because we really rejected the
places that society had for us.

00:04:31.700 --> 00:04:36.570 align:middle line:84%
And the more-- we are so
much more independent.

00:04:36.570 --> 00:04:41.150 align:middle line:84%
We are-- more entrepreneurs
are in their 20s and early 30s

00:04:41.150 --> 00:04:42.910 align:middle line:90%
and are making new rules.

00:04:42.910 --> 00:04:45.540 align:middle line:84%
And I think-- in that
way, I think it's great,

00:04:45.540 --> 00:04:47.190 align:middle line:90%
I think, in a way that we are.

00:04:47.190 --> 00:04:50.360 align:middle line:84%
But for a long time we
were rejected by society.

00:04:50.360 --> 00:04:54.680 align:middle line:84%
And now I think that this
sort of new expansive

00:04:54.680 --> 00:04:56.480 align:middle line:84%
thought that we
have sort of added--

00:04:56.480 --> 00:04:58.730 align:middle line:84%
as we grow and as we find
our place in the world,

00:04:58.730 --> 00:05:00.980 align:middle line:84%
I think that is
really catching on.

00:05:00.980 --> 00:05:01.820 align:middle line:90%
And I like that.

00:05:01.820 --> 00:05:02.420 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:05:02.420 --> 00:05:03.230 align:middle line:90%
Yeah, I do too.

00:05:03.230 --> 00:05:05.390 align:middle line:84%
It's very interesting
having young teachers.

00:05:05.390 --> 00:05:06.740 align:middle line:90%
>> It gives us all a place.

00:05:06.740 --> 00:05:10.460 align:middle line:84%
It gives us all a
place to fit in.

00:05:10.460 --> 00:05:14.440 align:middle line:90%
>> When did you know you had--

00:05:14.440 --> 00:05:16.920 align:middle line:90%
well, would I call it a gift?

00:05:16.920 --> 00:05:17.720 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes and no.

00:05:17.720 --> 00:05:19.280 align:middle line:84%
This is my whole thing
about psychic abilities.

00:05:19.280 --> 00:05:20.150 align:middle line:90%
Yes, we all have it.

00:05:20.150 --> 00:05:21.920 align:middle line:84%
But just like
basketball players--

00:05:21.920 --> 00:05:23.390 align:middle line:84%
I mean, we can all
play basketball.

00:05:23.390 --> 00:05:25.940 align:middle line:84%
But how many Michael Jordans
or how many professional NBA

00:05:25.940 --> 00:05:27.070 align:middle line:90%
players are out there?

00:05:27.070 --> 00:05:28.580 align:middle line:90%
So we all have it.

00:05:28.580 --> 00:05:31.470 align:middle line:90%
It just depends on what degree.

00:05:31.470 --> 00:05:33.893 align:middle line:84%
And I definitely
think this is a gift.

00:05:33.893 --> 00:05:35.810 align:middle line:84%
But just like an opera
singer, an opera singer

00:05:35.810 --> 00:05:36.650 align:middle line:90%
can have the greatest gift.

00:05:36.650 --> 00:05:38.608 align:middle line:84%
But unless they devote
their entire life to it,

00:05:38.608 --> 00:05:39.590 align:middle line:90%
they wouldn't know.

00:05:39.590 --> 00:05:41.730 align:middle line:84%
And I had my first
experience when I was three.

00:05:41.730 --> 00:05:42.530 align:middle line:90%
>> Three?

00:05:42.530 --> 00:05:43.640 align:middle line:90%
>> Three.

00:05:43.640 --> 00:05:46.140 align:middle line:84%
We were waiting for the nursery
school bus, my mother and I.

00:05:46.140 --> 00:05:47.460 align:middle line:90%
And the bus was late.

00:05:47.460 --> 00:05:49.260 align:middle line:10%
And I initially
looked up and said,

00:05:49.260 --> 00:05:51.630 align:middle line:10%
well, you know,
Ma, the bus is late

00:05:51.630 --> 00:05:54.153 align:middle line:10%
because Miss Mary broke
her arm last night.

00:05:54.153 --> 00:05:55.320 align:middle line:10%
And Miss Mary is the driver.

00:05:55.320 --> 00:05:56.790 align:middle line:10%
And sure enough,
the bus came late,

00:05:56.790 --> 00:05:57.840 align:middle line:10%
and Miss Mary wasn't driving.

00:05:57.840 --> 00:05:59.215 align:middle line:84%
And nobody could
figure out how I

00:05:59.215 --> 00:06:02.760 align:middle line:84%
knew that Miss Mary had broken
her arm the night before.

00:06:02.760 --> 00:06:03.750 align:middle line:90%
And that was it.

00:06:03.750 --> 00:06:06.310 align:middle line:84%
My parents were so freaked
by that, they were like--

00:06:06.310 --> 00:06:07.110 align:middle line:90%
>> Wow.

00:06:07.110 --> 00:06:09.600 align:middle line:84%
>> So I don't think I made
another prediction for many

00:06:09.600 --> 00:06:10.400 align:middle line:90%
years after that.

00:06:10.400 --> 00:06:11.950 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHS]

00:06:11.950 --> 00:06:14.730 align:middle line:84%
>> So then somewhere, you
picked up the thread again

00:06:14.730 --> 00:06:17.850 align:middle line:84%
in your life and you realized,
I have something here.

00:06:17.850 --> 00:06:19.650 align:middle line:90%
How did that manifest?

00:06:19.650 --> 00:06:22.170 align:middle line:84%
>> When I was growing up, it
manifested in that I would be

00:06:22.170 --> 00:06:23.790 align:middle line:84%
able to find things
around the house.

00:06:23.790 --> 00:06:27.090 align:middle line:84%
So my mother would say, you
know, go find the ice bucket.

00:06:27.090 --> 00:06:29.400 align:middle line:84%
And I would just be able
to find things in our very

00:06:29.400 --> 00:06:31.210 align:middle line:90%
cluttered closets in the house

00:06:31.210 --> 00:06:33.580 align:middle line:84%
And then when I
was in high school,

00:06:33.580 --> 00:06:37.342 align:middle line:84%
the little trend was to carry
a teeny little sports-type bag

00:06:37.342 --> 00:06:38.550 align:middle line:90%
with you to school every day.

00:06:38.550 --> 00:06:39.840 align:middle line:90%
And I would know--

00:06:39.840 --> 00:06:41.740 align:middle line:84%
every day, I would
know what to put in it.

00:06:41.740 --> 00:06:44.850 align:middle line:84%
So I would say, I need a
bobby pin, a safety pin,

00:06:44.850 --> 00:06:47.100 align:middle line:84%
an extra pen, a pencil, a
nail file, whatever, like,

00:06:47.100 --> 00:06:48.270 align:middle line:90%
the most obscure little things.

00:06:48.270 --> 00:06:49.440 align:middle line:84%
And people would
always say to me,

00:06:49.440 --> 00:06:51.273 align:middle line:84%
you know, you always
have everything, Stacy.

00:06:51.273 --> 00:06:54.720 align:middle line:84%
And my answer was always,
no, I only have what I need.

00:06:54.720 --> 00:06:57.030 align:middle line:84%
And I started
becoming fascinated

00:06:57.030 --> 00:06:58.860 align:middle line:84%
with all sorts of
occult, fascinated

00:06:58.860 --> 00:07:01.050 align:middle line:84%
with all sorts of
occult studies.

00:07:01.050 --> 00:07:05.107 align:middle line:84%
And I studied palm reading and
handwriting and those studies

00:07:05.107 --> 00:07:06.190 align:middle line:90%
when I was in high school.

00:07:06.190 --> 00:07:08.130 align:middle line:84%
And I guess it started
from there again.

00:07:08.130 --> 00:07:09.840 align:middle line:84%
>> You talk about
enhancing your life.

00:07:09.840 --> 00:07:13.230 align:middle line:84%
Was there a time when
your life was not good,

00:07:13.230 --> 00:07:15.610 align:middle line:84%
when you were unhappy,
when things around you

00:07:15.610 --> 00:07:16.410 align:middle line:90%
were miserable?

00:07:16.410 --> 00:07:20.040 align:middle line:84%
>> I can-- it was not so long
ago that I could tell you that

00:07:20.040 --> 00:07:22.320 align:middle line:90%
I was really unhappy.

00:07:22.320 --> 00:07:25.200 align:middle line:90%
I was working at MTV.

00:07:25.200 --> 00:07:27.060 align:middle line:84%
I was a writer and
associate producer.

00:07:27.060 --> 00:07:29.310 align:middle line:84%
And I didn't feel like my
career was going anywhere.

00:07:29.310 --> 00:07:33.090 align:middle line:84%
I was at least 15 pounds
heavier than I am now.

00:07:33.090 --> 00:07:35.550 align:middle line:84%
I can look back and say,
when I was 25, I looked 30.

00:07:35.550 --> 00:07:37.990 align:middle line:90%
I just was so unhappy.

00:07:37.990 --> 00:07:40.148 align:middle line:90%
And then I was fired.

00:07:40.148 --> 00:07:42.190 align:middle line:84%
And then the whole staff
was fired from the show.

00:07:42.190 --> 00:07:43.420 align:middle line:90%
And I had nothing to do.

00:07:43.420 --> 00:07:45.420 align:middle line:84%
And all my light bulbs
blew out in my apartment.

00:07:45.420 --> 00:07:46.560 align:middle line:84%
I had nothing to do
but sit and study

00:07:46.560 --> 00:07:48.150 align:middle line:84%
tarot card books
and spiritual books.

00:07:48.150 --> 00:07:50.180 align:middle line:84%
And that's what was my
spiritual awakening.

00:07:50.180 --> 00:07:53.550 align:middle line:84%
And I emerged from that
year, which was the end

00:07:53.550 --> 00:07:55.070 align:middle line:90%
of '91 to '92--

00:07:55.070 --> 00:07:57.150 align:middle line:84%
and I emerged from that
year at the end of '92

00:07:57.150 --> 00:07:59.310 align:middle line:90%
as a tarot card reader.

00:07:59.310 --> 00:08:01.980 align:middle line:84%
And I did stand-up
comedy and an actress.

00:08:01.980 --> 00:08:03.650 align:middle line:84%
And that's what started
me on my psychic

00:08:03.650 --> 00:08:05.450 align:middle line:90%
and my spiritual career.

00:08:05.450 --> 00:08:07.050 align:middle line:84%
And I remember when
I had no faith.

00:08:07.050 --> 00:08:09.095 align:middle line:84%
And this is why I tell
people in my lectures.

00:08:09.095 --> 00:08:10.720 align:middle line:84%
I was there, and I
know what it's like,

00:08:10.720 --> 00:08:12.337 align:middle line:84%
and it wasn't too
long ago, that when

00:08:12.337 --> 00:08:13.920 align:middle line:84%
you invite this
energy into your life,

00:08:13.920 --> 00:08:15.670 align:middle line:84%
it does all sorts
of amazing things.

00:08:15.670 --> 00:08:18.060 align:middle line:84%
And it makes you
more of who you are,

00:08:18.060 --> 00:08:19.290 align:middle line:90%
who you are supposed to be.

00:08:19.290 --> 00:08:21.910 align:middle line:84%
>> Is it a specific act
when you invite this energy

00:08:21.910 --> 00:08:22.710 align:middle line:90%
into your life--

00:08:22.710 --> 00:08:23.510 align:middle line:90%
>> I think so.

00:08:23.510 --> 00:08:26.310 align:middle line:84%
>> --because I think a lot of
people watching this now are

00:08:26.310 --> 00:08:29.920 align:middle line:90%
where you were not too long ago.

00:08:29.920 --> 00:08:33.760 align:middle line:84%
So their question
will be, what do I do?

00:08:33.760 --> 00:08:34.749 align:middle line:90%
Do I sit down?

00:08:34.749 --> 00:08:35.549 align:middle line:90%
Do I stand up?

00:08:35.549 --> 00:08:36.480 align:middle line:90%
Do I get on my knees?

00:08:36.480 --> 00:08:38.970 align:middle line:90%
How do I say, come on down?

00:08:38.970 --> 00:08:40.799 align:middle line:90%
>> I think however, actually.

00:08:40.799 --> 00:08:42.390 align:middle line:90%
I don't like rules.

00:08:42.390 --> 00:08:44.670 align:middle line:10%
And that's another thing
about the meditation books

00:08:44.670 --> 00:08:45.630 align:middle line:10%
and spiritual books out there.

00:08:45.630 --> 00:08:47.340 align:middle line:10%
You have to sit still,
and you can't move.

